{
	"instantcanvas": 1,
	"createdWith": "0.8.1",
	"title": "InstantCanvas — Presentation Mode",
	"presentation": {
		"aspect": "16:9",
		"theme": {
			"preset": "midnight"
		},
		"footer": {
			"left": "InstantCanvas",
			"right": "Slide {{slideNumber}} / {{totalSlides}}"
		}
	},
	"slides": [
		{
			"layout": "title",
			"title": "Presentation Mode",
			"subtitle": "A deck is a canvas whose envelope carries slides[]",
			"author": "HappySkills",
			"date": "July 2026",
			"notes": "Open on this. The deck IS a canvas — one JSON file, seven layouts, no packer. SPEAKER-NOTE-MARKER"
		},
		{
			"layout": "section",
			"title": "Why a deck?",
			"subtitle": "Slides are assigned, never flowed"
		},
		{
			"layout": "content",
			"title": "What you get",
			"body": [
				{
					"type": "markdown",
					"text": "- **Seven layouts** — title, section, content, two-column, quadrant, statement, closing\n- **Charts fill their region** — a lone chart gets the whole stage\n- **The theme system, unchanged** — 22 presets, dark decks first-class\n- **Print to landscape PDF** — one page per slide"
				},
				{
					"type": "kpi",
					"cards": [
						{
							"label": "Layouts",
							"value": 7,
							"format": "number"
						},
						{
							"label": "New deps",
							"value": 0,
							"format": "number"
						},
						{
							"label": "Agent CSS",
							"value": 0,
							"format": "number"
						}
					]
				}
			],
			"notes": "Lead with \"no new dependencies\" — that is the whole ethos."
		},
		{
			"layout": "content",
			"title": "A chart fills the slide",
			"footer": false,
			"body": [
				{
					"type": "chart",
					"kind": "bar",
					"title": "Revenue by region ($000s)",
					"data": [
						{
							"region": "APAC",
							"rev": 42
						},
						{
							"region": "EMEA",
							"rev": 61
						},
						{
							"region": "AMER",
							"rev": 25
						},
						{
							"region": "LATAM",
							"rev": 14
						}
					],
					"encoding": {
						"x": "region",
						"y": "rev"
					}
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"layout": "two-column",
			"title": "Before vs after",
			"leftHeading": "Admin panel",
			"rightHeading": "InstantCanvas",
			"split": "1-1",
			"left": [
				{
					"type": "markdown",
					"text": "Build a dashboard nobody asked for.\n\nMaintain it for a year.\n\nSecrets pasted into chat."
				}
			],
			"right": [
				{
					"type": "markdown",
					"text": "Render the answer on the fly.\n\nDiscard it, or keep the JSON.\n\nValues go straight to disk."
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"layout": "quadrant",
			"title": "The design commitments",
			"cells": [
				{
					"heading": "Separation of concerns",
					"blocks": [
						{
							"type": "markdown",
							"text": "The LLM wrangles data; the runtime owns rendering."
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"heading": "Lean context",
					"blocks": [
						{
							"type": "markdown",
							"text": "Progressive disclosure — an 8 KB index, one schema on demand."
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"heading": "Deterministic validation",
					"blocks": [
						{
							"type": "markdown",
							"text": "A program decides correctness, and its errors teach the fix."
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"heading": "Zero dependencies",
					"blocks": [
						{
							"type": "markdown",
							"text": "Plain Node, vendored browser files, no build step."
						}
					]
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"layout": "statement",
			"text": "Death to the admin panel.",
			"attribution": "— The mission",
			"background": {
				"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
				"size": "cover",
				"position": "center",
				"scrim": {
					"color": "#05070d",
					"opacity": 0.42
				},
				"ink": "#ffffff"
			},
			"notes": "Pause. This is the line to leave them with."
		},
		{
			"layout": "closing",
			"title": "Thank you",
			"subtitle": "npx -y @happyskillsai/instant-canvas catalog presentation"
		}
	]
}
